24/05/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Security forces killed four members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) on Friday (May 22nd) during a military operation in the southeastern province of Diyarbakir, the army said in a statement Saturday. Two of the PKK militants were women, the statement added. The terrorists were believed to be among those responsible for an attack on a military vehicle in April that killed nine Turkish soldiers. In Friday's operation, troops seized Kalashnikov assault rifles, ammunition, hand grenades and PKK documents. (Vatan - 24/05/09; CNN Turk, Dogan news agency, Hurriyet, Reuters, DPA, AP, Xinhua - 23/05/09)
